From: UML static-link enablement
Subject: [PATCH] um: vector: drop false MAY_HAVE_RUNTIME_DEPS select

The UML_NET_VECTOR driver is marked `select MAY_HAVE_RUNTIME_DEPS`,
which forces CONFIG_STATIC_LINK off. The intent of that guard is to
prevent a static binary that secretly dlopen()s a host shared library
(such a binary could never work without the host .so).

VECTOR does not do this. Inspection of arch/um/drivers/vector_user.c and
vector_transports.c shows:

  * tap / raw / unix / fd / hybrid transports use only raw syscalls
    (socket, ioctl(TUNSETIFF), epoll, sendmmsg, ...);
  * the `vde` transport does NOT link libvdeplug and does NOT dlopen it --
    it spawns the external `vde_plug` helper via run_helper() and talks to
    it over an AF_UNIX socketpair, so no host .so is embedded or required;
  * the only libc surface beyond plain syscalls is getaddrinfo(), which in
    a static glibc build is resolved at link time (files + dns backends
    compiled in) and never dlopen()s NSS modules.

Therefore a fully-static UML+VECTOR binary has zero runtime .so
requirement and runs on any same-arch host (glibc or musl/Alpine).

Drop the bogus select so STATIC_LINK and UML_NET_VECTOR can coexist.

Signed-off-by: quangdz-comeback <204571370+quangdz-comeback@users.noreply.github.com>
---

diff --git a/arch/um/drivers/Kconfig b/arch/um/drivers/Kconfig
index 6a0354ca0..0a86b4f95 100644
--- a/arch/um/drivers/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/um/drivers/Kconfig
@@ -126,7 +126,6 @@ menu "UML Network Devices"
 
 config UML_NET_VECTOR
 	bool "Vector I/O high performance network devices"
-	select MAY_HAVE_RUNTIME_DEPS
 	help
 	  This User-Mode Linux network driver uses multi-message send
 	  and receive functions. The host running the UML guest must have
